 a pleasing terror the complete supernatural writings  ashtree press contains  stories the  stories from collected ghost stories plus the  tales published after this and the  from the fenstanton witch and others also includes some related nonfiction by james and some writings about him by others it is the only complete published collection of his ghost fiction although of the unfinished tales and drafts revised versions have subsequently appeared on the ghosts and scholars website following further deciphering of the notoriously illegible handwriting of james manuscripts count magnus and other ghost stories  edited with an introduction and notes by s t joshi the haunted dolls house and other ghost stories  edited with an introduction and notes by s t joshi curious warnings the great ghost stories of m r james  edited reparagraphing the text for the modern reader by stephen jones guidebooksedit abbeys  suffolk and norfolk  childrens booksedit the five jars  as translator fortytwo stories by hans christian andersen translated and with an introduction by m r james  notesedit  a b c briggs julia  james montague rhodes in sullivan jack ed the penguin encyclopedia of horror and the supernatural new york viking press isbn   a b c d e f cox michael  introduction casting the runes and other ghost stories by m r james oxford oxford university press pp xi–xxx isbn   a b c d e jones darryl  introduction collected ghost stories by m r james oxford oxford university press p xii isbn   james montague rhodes jmsmr a cambridge alumni database university of cambridge   benson edward frederic  our family affairs  london new york toronto and melbourne cassell and company ltd p    a b james mr preface to more ghost stories of an antiquary in joshi st ed  count magnus and other ghost stories the complete ghost stories of mr james volume  pt  penguin books  james m r  introduction in collins v h ghosts and marvels a selection of uncanny tales from daniel defoe to algernon blackwood london